        <p>The term <italic>t</italic><sup><italic>L</italic> + 1</sup>occurs when <italic>j</italic>â=â<italic>L</italic>âââ<italic>M</italic>âââ<italic>K</italic>.If <italic>j</italic>â&lt;â0, this coefficient is 0. If <italic>j</italic>ââ¥â0, this coefficient is
<inline-formula><mml:math id="M82" name="1471-2105-13-238-i83" overflow="scroll"><mml:mfenced><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mi>M</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>)</mml:mo><mml:mfenced open="(" close=")"><mml:mfrac linethickness="0"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>L</mml:mi><mml:mo>â</mml:mo><mml:mi>K</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>M</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac></mml:mfenced></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math></inline-formula>.</p>
        <p>4.Evaluate <italic>E</italic>[<italic>N</italic>] to obtain Equation (A9): </p>
        <p>
          <disp-formula>
            <mml:math id="M83" name="1471-2105-13-238-i84" overflow="scroll">
