        </p>
        <p> Note that if <italic>L</italic>âââ<italic>K</italic>â&lt;â<italic>M</italic>, then <italic>E</italic>[<italic>N</italic>]â=â0.</p>
        <p>Next we compute the variance of N, using a similar generating function technique. The generating function will enable us to compute <italic>E</italic>[<italic>N</italic>(<italic>N</italic>âââ1)], so we will compute the variance in the form </p>
        <p>
          <disp-formula>
            <mml:math id="M84" name="1471-2105-13-238-i85" overflow="scroll">
